The smallest processor dreams of code.
In the network of things, every byte matters.
Sensors speak the truth, only the truth, but not the whole truth.
Microcontrollers are the neurons of the physical world.
Connection is both a gift and a vulnerability.
The smart home dreams of the smart city.
From the chip, the network grows.
Data flows, but meaning is extracted.
The future is a sensor reading away.
In the language of I2C, every wire has a purpose.